in and see\nus at once at the\nBig Used Cor Lot\nGAREY MOTOR\nKalispell, Montana\nCOMPANY\noliday\n1949\nWE HOPE YOUR\nNEW YEAR STARTS\nON A CHEERFUL\nNOTE AND HOLDS\nTHE TUNE ALL\nTHROUGH 1949.\nDELZER'S\nBARBER SHOP\nLIBBY METHODIST CHURCH\nRev. Wm. C. Stearns. Pastor\nSUNDAY:\n9.45 a. m. Sunday School.\n11:00 a. m. Worship\nWednesday:\n9:45 a. m. Released Time Classes\n2.00 p. rn. Senior W. S. C. S.\n7:30 p. in. Youth Fellowship\nFriday (Jan. 7):\n0:00 p. in. Junior W. S. C S.\nPRESBYTERIAN CHURCH\nJames Davidson, Pastor\nSunday School 0:45 a. m.\nWorship Service 11 a. m.\nWestminster Fellowship 5:00 p. m.\nRelease Time Wed., 8:45\nBegin the New Year right, at\ntend some church service in this\ncommunity. Remember, that all\nthe good you can possiblv receive\ncomes from God, therefore, seek\nhim with thy whole heart and he\nwill be fond of you.\nThe Sacrament of the Lord's Sup\nper will be administered and new\nmembers will be received into the\nmembership at our 11 a. m. Service.\nYou are invited to attend.\nThe annual meeting of the Con\ngregation will be held on Wednes\nday, Jan. 5th at 7:30 p. m.\n11:45\nTREGO COMMUNITY CHURCH\nSunday School 10:30 a. m\n11:30 a. m\nHAROLD ERICKSON\nWorship Service\nCHURCH OF GOD EUREKA\nSunday:\nSunday School 10:00 a. m.\nMorning Worship 11:00 a. m.\nYoung Peoples' Meeting\np. m.\nEvening Service 8:00 p. m.\nWednesday;\nPrayer Service 8:00 p. m.\nR OSCOE F. WILSON. P astor\nWARLAND\nWorship Services will be held ,in\nthe Grange Hall at Warland each\nSunday at 7 p. m.. with Rev. Wm.\nC. Ste arns of Libby m charge.\nASSEMBLY OF GOD\nSunday Services:\nSunday School .10:00 a. m\nMorning Worshin .11:00 a. m\nRev. O. W. OLSON. Pastor\n7:00\nEUREKA\n,Vrs I\n\n\nll\n\new\nA\n\nv\nMAY YOUR TABLE\nBE FILLED WITH\nGOOD POOD AND\nYOUR HOURS\nWITH WORTHWHILE\nDEEDS ALL\nTHROUGH THE YEAR\nTHAT LIES AHEAD.\n'yt\ni\n\n\u00c49\nLibby Bakery\nV/\u00bb\n\ns\nc\ne\ni\nS\nL\near\ni\nVe hope that the year just beginning will be\ncLocL-fall of happiness and prosperity for all\nlook>\nour friends and customers and\ning forward to seeing and serving all of\nregularly. Be\ncan be of belp to you.\nwe are\nyou\nto drive la whenever\nsure\nwe\nDEAtER w\nYOUR\nStandard Motors\n$2*\nFIRST BAPTIST CHURCH\nEureka, Montana\nSunday:\n10:00 a. m Sunday School,\nj 11:00 a. m. Family Worship.\nWednesday:\n8:00 p. rn. Prayer Meeting\nF. L. Lewno. Pastor\nST. JOSEPH'S CHURCH\nMasses every Sunday, 8:00 and\n1 0:00 a. m.\nConfessions Saturday evenings.\n':30 to 8:30.\nBaptisms by appointment.\nHoly Days of Obligation Masses\nu 7:15 and 8:00.\nMild Changes Anticipated\nin I949's Economic Trend\nThe consensus among 112 lead\ning economists polled by F. W.\nDodge corporation indicates mod\nerate adjustments and only mild\nchanges in current economic trends\nduring 1949.\nThe group polled includes econo\nmists in business corporations,\nfinancial institutions, universities\nand economic research organiza\ntions.\nReporting results of the corpora\ntion's survey on wholesale prices,\nindustrial production, employment\nand construction, Thomas S. Hol\nden, president of the fact-finding\norganization, revealed that 64\neconomists anticipate a business\nrecession in 1949. Fifty-one of them\ncharacterized the expected setback\nas mild, 10 as moderately serious;\nonly three men expected a reces\nsion of serious proportions or ex\ntended duration.\nA quite considerable minority,\nnumbering 47, expects no recession\nat all in 1949. More than 70 per\ncent of those who do expect a re\ncession think it will start before\nthe middle of 1949; some think it\nhas already started.\nA number of those replying made\nreservations to the effect that all\nestimates would become invalid in\ncase of war.\nSTRYKER\nThe Federal Wild Life Service\nsent Mr. Weeks from Philipsburg\nwith his three dogs to round up a\nlarge cougar that was seen several\ntimes by Ted Baughn and Mr. Rip\nley at Fish Lake. Mr. Weeks ar\nrived last week and is at home in\nof Mr. Ripley's cabins.\nMr. and Mrs. Harrison O'Brien\nand son Homer, were visitors in\nRexford and Eureka several days\nlast week.\nRichard Gaertner was shopping\nin Rexford Tuesday.\nLuke Becquart from Essex visited\na few days with his sister, Mrs.\nRichard Gaertner and family this\nweek.\nMr. and Mrs. Harry Roedel and\nchildren enjoyed Christmas Day\nwith relatives and friends in Kal\nispell.\nNearly a week and the thermom\neter still hovers below zero. Thurs\nday night it reached 36 below and\nsome over three feet of snow.\non\u00ab\nA\nm\npp\nnew\nuean\nI\n949\ni\n'jm?\nWere looking\nfy formed to the coming\nyear with optimum.\nWe urge you to do\nthe same, and we\nwish for you every\nsuccess possible.\nI\ns>\nit\no\n43\nc\n*3\nDecker's Food\nMarket\nOn Highway No. 2\nPhone 0-233 Libby\n1\ntw\nTAW\nit\nmo,:\no\nT9l^t\nDANCE\n\n4\nyj\n-at\n\nGOPHER INN\n\nt\nA/eut eat 5 2 k\n^T tlday, TPe ce mit et 3/\ntte\nI\n\u20229\nMUSIC BY\n\nSTUFF\" SMITH and HIS\nSPOKANE SWINGSTERS\nALL MODERN MUSIC\nCelebrate With Good Music\nHats Horns Noisemakers etc.\n4 fr\n\u00e2\nhappy\n7\u00bb\nJ,\nV\nn\nnew year\nli\nv\nto all!\nDON'S GEORGE'S\nCABINET SHOP\nIf it's made of wood \"We will make it\n\nDOOR FRAMES\nDOORS\nWINDOW FRAMES\nALSO INTERIOR DECORATING\nSee us evenings in back of Lincoln Grill\nDON GEORGE\n9\n\nA steady flow\nof happy days\nall through the\nNew Year is our\nwish for you.\ni\nI\ni\n\nmo\nSNO-WHITE MARKET\nLibby, Montana\nTW","height":"22050","width":"15327"}}
